n.quantum computing

Proton is the world’s only accessible neuromorphic quantum computing cloud for solving real-world problems, at scale.

Global-2000

Proton is a DePIN platform for neuromorphic quantum computing, based on an innovative new blockchain protocol.

It consists of participating Proof-of-Useful-Work (PoUW) miners that constitute a decentralised n.quantum computing network which is capable of computing quantum computing algorithms, featuring quantum-entanglement and -tunnelling effects, at scale.

Without the limitations of traditional quantum computing, it can solve real-world problems, made possible with our proprietary algorithm ProtonSolve.

All this is wrapped in a sustainable and long term business model.

Proton Solve

Global-2000

Proton is a DePIN platform for neuromorphic quantum computing, based on an innovative new blockchain protocol.

It consists of participating Proof-of-Useful-Work (PoUW) miners that constitute a decentralised n.quantum computing network which is capable of computing quantum computing algorithms, featuring quantum-entanglement and -tunnelling effects, at scale.

Without the limitations of traditional quantum computing, it can solve real-world problems, made possible with our proprietary algorithm ProtonSolve.

All this is wrapped in a sustainable and long term business model.

  • Quantum computing algorithms for machine learning harness the power of quantum mechanics to enhance various aspects of machine learning tasks. As both, quantum computing and neuromorphic computing are sharing similar features, these algorithms can also be computed efficiently on the Proton platform directly within Python – but without the limitations of quantum machines.

Uber Tech That Works

  • Quantum computing algorithms for machine learning harness the power of quantum mechanics to enhance various aspects of machine learning tasks. As both, quantum computing and neuromorphic computing are sharing similar features, these algorithms can also be computed efficiently on the Proton platform directly within Python – but without the limitations of quantum machines.

Uber Tech That Works

A Fair Start

A Fair Start

No Premine

Truly fair launch in September 2022 with no ICO, no pre-mining and pre-allocation of coins to the team or investors.

Finite Supply

A maximum of 110.000.000 PTN utility coins with a deflationary emission schedule.

Sustainable

With Proton, mining is channelled through solving real-world problems, with real, proven results.

LEADErSHIP TEAM

The Proton team consists of 35 people, dedicated to innovation and excellence.
Our leadership team is comprised of distinguished individuals at the forefront of
their respective fields, each contributing unique expertise and vision.

Daniela Herrmann

Co-founder

As the founder of the Topan® Ecosystem, Daniela brings to Proton a profound expertise in sustainability, fintech, blockchain, crypto, big data analytics, and quantitative investment strategies. Her visionary leadership and commitment to Triple-E® excellence form the cornerstone of our mission to integrate technological innovation with sustainable practices.

Adam Neumann

Global Head of Innovation

and Science

With a Ph.D. in artificial intelligence and neuromorphic networks, Adam has been instrumental in shaping Proton's approach to AI, neuromorphic computing and quantum algorithms. His work, marked by numerous peer-reviewed publications, underpins our innovation strategies and scientific endeavours.

Clifford Mapp

Global Head of Ecosystem

Development & Information

Security

A recognized authority in blockchain and IT security, Clifford's pioneering work has been critical in developing Proton's secure and robust technological ecosystem. His expertise ensures the integrity and resilience of our platforms and services.

Charles Newton Price

Global Head of Business

Development & Partnerships

Charles's extensive experience as a technology professional and entrepreneur enhances our business development strategies. His leadership is pivotal in forging strategic partnerships and expanding Proton's presence in the global market.

Ivan Petliokha

Global Head of Platform

Development

Ivan's deep knowledge in commercial development, blockchain, and DeFi is vital to the continuous evolution of Proton's platforms. His contributions have been central to our innovation in financial technologies and services.

Onur Oztaskiran

Global Head of Design

With nearly two decades of experience in design, Onur's expertise in human interface, product, and experience design is crucial in making our technologies accessible and user-friendly. His leadership ensures that design remains at the heart of our innovation process.

Davey G.A. de Kort

Global Head of Support

Davey's experience in digital assets, RWA tokenization, and cryptography supports Proton's commitment to secure and reliable services. His leadership in support operations enhances our customer experience and trust.

Gregory Carson

Advisor, Strategic Affairs

As the managing director of Humla Ventures, Greg brings a wealth of experience in company building, investments, and strategic partnerships. His insights are invaluable in navigating technological changes and scaling operations.

Daniel Voicu

Advisor, Technology & Research

Revered as one of the original godfathers of our algorithms, Daniel's 18+ years at senior executive levels in companies like Microsoft, and as a core tech stack developer of C#, brings a level of technical mastery and insight that is rare and invaluable.

Monika Kindle

Managing Director &

Head of Administration

Monika's decades-long experience in administration ensures the smooth operation of Proton's daily activities and supports the overall efficiency and effectiveness of our team.

Ethical Committee

The Proton Ethical Committee is tasked with overseeing the ethical integrity of select Proton n.quantum computing inquiries. The Ethical Committee’s role is critical to ensuring that n.quantum activities adhere to ethical standards.

Sally Chu

United Kingdom

An acclaimed World Women's Organization award recipient, Sally Chu is the founder of the Oneness Art Platform. She has a rich 30-year history in the art world, with a vast network extending from across Europe and Asia. With deep roots in HK/China and highly respected by the community, Sally is well-versed in bridging the art and business worlds

Dr. Mikael Lind

Sweden

Dr. Mikael Lind holds the unique title of Adjunct Professor in Maritime Informatics. As a renowned expert, he contributes to forums such as the World Economic Forum, Europe’s DTLF, and UN/CEFACT. His pioneering work in maritime informatics, supply chain resilience, and maritime decarbonization has established him as a thought leader, shaping the future of sustainable transport.

Wolfgang Lehmacher

Germany

Wolfgang Lehmacher is a strategic thinker and business leader in the global supply chain and logistics ecosystem. With extensive expertise spanning across continents, Wolfgang is a renowned advisor, business mentor, judge, and author. He has served as Head of Supply Chain and Transport Industries at the World Economic Forum and has contributed to major change initiatives in the industry.

Sharron L. McPherson

South Africa

Sharron McPherson is a vanguard in climate and development finance, adept at bridging public finance with capital markets. Her expertise extends over 30 years, starting, building, and navigating businesses through competitive and complex regulatory environments, influencing high-impact investment and advising global entities like the World Bank and African Development Bank.

Chris Luebkeman

Switzerland

Chris Luebkeman is a world renowned futurist, Head of the Strategic Foresight Hub at ETH Zurich and founder of [y]our2040. His career spans disciplines and geographies, marked by his time teaching at renowned institutions like the University of Oregon and MIT. His work in digital transformation and future thinking led him to Arup in London, where he founded the Foresight, Innovation, and Incubation teams. A champion of change, Chris serves on several influential advisory boards, sharing his vision for a regenerative future and fostering innovation at every level.

Revenue generation

Revenue from Proton compute has been growing consistenly since launch, surpassing 160k PTN and growing on a month-month basis.

TELECOMMUNICATION

First telecommunication companies are applying quantum algoriths on Proton to optimise the positioning of antennas, increasing coverage and minimizing overhead costs.
